The paper proposes a sparse recovery algorithm using Bayesian hypothesis test and belief propagation, which are commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of sparse-binary sensing matrices, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and compressed sensing (cs.MM). The paper mentions noise-robustness and quantization effect, which are topics in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.SP, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.NA.
